<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-454-137  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 454 137.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computers in Healthcare  Oct 1990 v11 n10 p31(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Simplification of mortality case review. (case study of St.andO;Francis Regional Medical Center)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gillespie, Joe D.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>St. Francis Regional Medical Center in Wichita, Kansas employs asimplified mortality case review process to counter increasingdemands to examine actual medical records from various specialinterest groups.andP;  The simplified process involves a case summaryreport that is reviewed by medical staff office personnel and thenrouted to the appropriate department and/or physician wherespecific criteria are used to determine if an expired patient'sactual medical record must be analyzed.andP;  Cases involving any ofthe following screening criteria require the original medicalrecord for further review: deaths with complications listed in thefinal diagnosis, deaths occurring during the first 24 hours ofhospitalization and discrepancies between admitting and finaldiagnoses.andP;  St. Francis' case summary approach has been inoperation since 1987 and has reduced significantly the need foractual medical records.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     KansasPatientsQuality ControlMedical RecordsClinical MedicineData BasesRecords ManagementCase Study.andO;Feature:   illustrationforms.andO;Caption:   How to document the review process. (forms)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>